Long receptive field: Maestro¶

  • 30 layers
  • Dilation resets to 1 every 3 layers
  • Kernel size = 3
  • Receptive field = 6.139 seconds
  • 9 days of training
In [2]:
utils.show_examples('long-maestro-examples', lambda data, rate : display(Audio(data=data, rate=rate)))
utils.show_losses('Loss curves', *utils.load_loss('long-maestro-train.txt'), utils.load_loss('long-maestro-dev.txt')[1])

Short receptive field: Maestro¶

  • 24 layers
  • Dilation resets to 1 every 4 layers
  • Kernel size = 3
  • Receptive field = 0.505 seconds
  • 14 days of training
